HIV Prevalence in Chiradzulu

For a detailed methodology on how these maps were created, please refer to the supplementary material.

District Map

The following interactive map shows HIV prevalence estimates across Chiradzulu at the district, traditional authority, and 1x1km pixel levels. Health facility locations and details are also shown.

Traditional authorities

The following table lists HIV prevalence among 15 to 49-year olds and population across the same age range for all traditional authorities in Chiradzulu.

Traditional Authority HIV Prevalence Viral load suppression HIV viraemia
Chiradzulu Boma 11.2% (6.1 to 18.0%) 89.4% (75.1 to 97.1%) 1.2% (0.3 to 3.2%)
Chitera 9.7% (5.4 to 15.9%) 86.0% (67.3 to 96.2%) 1.3% (0.3 to 3.5%)
Kadewere 10.2% (5.9 to 16.7%) 86.8% (69.1 to 96.2%) 1.3% (0.3 to 3.6%)
Likoswe 11.2% (6.3 to 18.4%) 85.9% (67.4 to 95.7%) 1.6% (0.4 to 4.2%)
Mpama 10.8% (6.2 to 17.6%) 86.4% (68.9 to 96.0%) 1.5% (0.4 to 3.9%)
Nchema 9.8% (5.2 to 16.2%) 87.6% (70.5 to 96.7%) 1.2% (0.3 to 3.3%)
Nkalo 11.7% (6.7 to 19.0%) 87.9% (71.4 to 96.7%) 1.4% (0.3 to 3.6%)
STA Mpunga 10.2% (5.6 to 17.0%) 86.1% (67.3 to 96.1%) 1.4% (0.4 to 3.6%)
STA Onga 10.9% (6.0 to 17.8%) 88.1% (71.6 to 96.8%) 1.3% (0.3 to 3.5%)
STA Sandareki 9.7% (5.4 to 16.4%) 87.8% (71.1 to 96.5%) 1.2% (0.3 to 3.2%)
